Former world number-one Ivan Lendl warmed up  for next week's French Open Tennis Championships in Paris by reaching the  final of the clay-court exhibition tournament here Friday.
Lendl, 34, beat Paul Haarhuis of the Netherlands 6-2, 6-4.
He now plays another Dutchman, Jacco Eltingh, for the title on Saturday.  Eltingh beat Frenchman Stephane Simian 6-2, 3-6, 7-6.
